WebService-AbuseIPDB 0.02
-------------------------

Released 23nd January 2020

DESCRIPTION
-----------

This distribution is a client for version 2 of the AbuseIPDB API as
described at https://docs.abuseipdb.com/ and it may be used to check the
current status of an IP address in that database or submit reports of
nefarious activity.

This is alpha code. Expect the internals and interface to change.


INSTALLATION
------------

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION
-------------------------

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc WebService::AbuseIPDB

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs and suggest improvements here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=WebService-AbuseIPDB

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/pod/WebService-AbuseIPDB/


